               <msContents>
                  <summary> A little-known author named Qābil Rām <addName>Āfarīn</addName> Lāhūrī
                     (1660–1741) originally composed this Persian translation of the Punjabi
                        <title>Qiṣṣah-i Hīr va Rānjhan</title> (Tale of Hīr va Rānjhan) in 1118 AH
                     (1707 CE) shortly before the death of the Mughal ruler, Emperor
                        <persName>‘Ālamgīr I (b. 1616, r. 1658–1707)</persName>. A scribe named
                        <persName>Mīr ‘Ubayd Allāh <addName>Shīrīn Raqam</addName>
                        Sirhindī</persName> completed this manuscript on <date>25 Shawwāl 1164 AH
                        (16 Sept. 1751 CE)</date> and a painter added thirteen finely executed
                     paintings, the style of which indicates possible execution in <placeName
                        cert="medium" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001541"
                        key="place_7001541">Hyderabad</placeName>, approximately ten years after the
                     author's death.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_896-item1">
                     <author key="person_33279771" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/33279771/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Qābil Rām <addName
                              type="penname">Āfarīn</addName> Lāhūrī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">قابل رام آفرین لاهوری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20041" change="#ids-cleanup">Qiṣṣah-i
                        Hīr va Rānjhan</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_20041" change="#ids-cleanup">قصه هیر و
                        رانجهن</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> بنام چمن ساذ ناز و نیاز * که خار نیازش بود سر ناز</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"><locus from="40b" to="40b"> برگ ۴۰پ (folio
                           40b):</locus> گلستان کن صبح پ شامم توی * چمن بنا ز عیش مدامم
                        توی</explicit>
                     <colophon><locus from="40b" to="40b"> برگ ۴۰پ (folio 40b):</locus> باتمام رسید
                        قصه هیر و رنجهن اتخاب نموده قابل رام بیست و پنجم شهر شوال المعظم سال دوازدهم
                        پادشاه غزی محمد شاه موافق سنه ۱۱۴۲ یکهزار و یکصد و چهل و دو هجری کاتب میر
                        عبید الله شیرین رقم سرہندی </colophon>
                     <colophon>Completed by <persName>Mīr ‘Ubayd Allāh <addName>Shīrīn
                              Raqam</addName> Sirhindī</persName> on <date>25 Shawwāl 1164 AH (16
                           Sept. 1751 CE)</date>, in the twelfth year of Muḥammad Shāh's
                        reign.</colophon>
                     <note>A note at the end records the number of couplets in Indic <hi>sīyāq</hi>
                        numerals.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Textblock of medium-weight, straight-grained, externally sized and
                           polished, buff-coloured <material>paper</material> handmade in the
                              <placeName cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208"
                              key="place_7000208">Indian subcontinent</placeName> with ~19 laid
                           lines per 20 mm and no discernible chain lines, and average thickness of
                           122 microns taken from the first ten folios. Subsequently spray-painted
                           with a stencil in two-column layout in <material>gold. The sprayed
                              columns measure ~ 38mm in width.. </material></support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="folio" quantity="40">40 folios, 2 flyleaves (ff. i + 40 +
                              i)</measure>. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>288</height>
                              <width>177</width>
                              <depth>0.122</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>198</height>
                              <width>91</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>

                        <foliation xml:id="original">Hindu-Arabic numerals added to the upper-left
                           corners of the a sides throughout.</foliation>


                        <collation> Quaternions throughout 5IV(40). <catchwords>Catchwords
                              throughout most of the lower-left corners of the b
                           sides.</catchwords></collation>


                        <condition>In fair condition, with moderate water and insect damage and
                           historical repairs throughout.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>


